"Version: 1.9 (Development)

Please submit bugs via github: https://github.com/rusher81572/s3 

What is new in this release? 

1. Object Explorer will only show the first 1000 objects. Added a button "Show all objects" to display all the objects.
2. Syncing now syncs subdirectories.
3. For stability, delete operations are limited to 500.
4. Object explorer displays the total number of objects in the bucket.
5. For stabiity, a manual refresh of the objects with the search button is required to ensure that delete threads are finished. 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Version: 1.8

1. Deletes are now threaded.
2. Fixed a bug to allow multiple "Sync to S3" operations without reloading objects manually.
3. Toolbar in "Object Explorer" is now persistent when scrolling.
4. Secret key contains special characters for privacy reasons.
5. Fixed a bug when creating buckets on AWS.
6. Fixed a bug when deleting an object from the search results.

* Special note for Background Sync users *

Background Sync will not recursively sync directories.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Version: 1.7.3

1. Logging window scrolls automatically now.
2. Support for @ in the object name.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Version: 1.7.2

1. Fixed a bug with background sync.
2. Background Sync is now working properly.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Version: 1.7.1 

1. Code improvements.
2. Fixed bug with displaying images.
3. Fixed bug with playing music.


If you plan on using this feature, background sync will automatically use the first account entry in ~/s3.config

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Version: 1.7

Code improvements.
Support for aborting Uploads and Downloads.
PUT and GET operations are done in a separate thread.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Version: 1.6

Faster search. 
Settings is now the default startup tab so the user can quickly choose the S3 account to load.
Upon selecting a bucket. Object Explorer will automatically load and display the objects.
Improvement to accounts. Single click to load account and buckets.
